Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udalsorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalsorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/18/02 4:00:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I don't need to be on a PvP server to know </span><hr size=1> For a while I was really opposed to the whole manaburn thing, even had a heated debate with my wizzy friend after his manaburn group nuked Gore.<br>
<br>
In the end it comes down to this, mid-tier guilds (either by choice or starting out) can now get two good friends and kill Gore, Sev and Rage to epic the appropriate classes w/o having to invite half the known world (overkill, but you get the drift.)  From talking to the wizzies, they were amused by it, but the type of people that are 59 and have spent the time for AAXP to get it, they typically aren't as greed-centric as the mid50s (where the leveling gets hard.<br>
<br>
Quiet frankly I wish my guild had one of two of these guys myself.  Then I know we'd be getting the damn cleric epics, so I have a chance at getting mine (don't care what you think about their worth.. =) ).<br>
<br>
Sure you can have a group of dinks that blast Sev every time he spawns, but honestly I think that after doing that once or twice they'd pretty much be persona non-grata for most of the higher level functions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/18/02 4:14:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defenseless you say?</span><hr size=1> We were asked our opinion.  We voiced it.  Just because you disagree doesn't make us wrong.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A> at: 7/18/02 4:20:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukilzalot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilzalot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/18/02 4:42:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defenseless you say?</span><hr size=1> Just my opinion.... make MOBS that have less than 50k HP invul. to MB.  I think is is retarded that 1 group can kill Trak, Sev, Gore, etc...  Kinda takes the fun and challenge out of it IMHO. <p>Kilzalot Drachonis... 59 Warrior of The Syndicate - Tarew Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/18/02 4:48:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defenseless you say?</span><hr size=1> Heyas-<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Clearly no one that has posted about this has experience the joy of being on a PvP server as a warrior in a so-so guild with access to so-so gear getting mana burned by Uber_Guild_Wizzy_04.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Just a couple thoughts from a blubie server type, but the DA effect from a SBI or (dain scroll if you ever managed to get a ringwar done on a pvp server!) might be just the thing for that situation.  Also, since MB is like a 6 second cast, perhaps stun idols from stonebrunt or mojo sticks (cold one has an iterrupt on it I think) from WL?  Last I heard MB could be interrupted like any other spell right?<br>
<br>
How common is worn see-invis gear for casters?  Something as simple as a instant cast invis potion would be enough to stop a nuker without it...<br>
<br>
Obviously a losing proposition in the long run (wizzie MB recycles in an hour or so, stuff I mentioned has to be farmed/bought/equipped in time/etc) but it WOULD be a lot of fun to live through one occasionally and go pummel the nuker. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umrollins.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mrollins</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/19/02 11:05:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defenseless you say?</span><hr size=1> Typically when this is has happened to me is when I am travelling somewhere solo and not in a group. And as I noted I really don't have uber gear. So if I have no see invis up, plus SOW, then on a PVP server you are pretty much burnt toast. (Pun intended.). You get the so and so is casting a spell on you. And then &quot;loading, please wait&quot;. Invising yourself with a potion won't help because on a PVP server every caster that has 1/2 a brain will always have see invis cast on themselves.<br>
<br>
Heck one time I was AFK sitting on top of a wizzy spire prong<br>
(Levitate will let you do that...) waiting for a port up to the nexus. And some twit from pandemonium mana burned me.<br>
<br>
The wizzy spires are often camped by caster PvPers because they know us melee types often use the nexus to ghetto port around.<br>
<br>
So. I guess the best advice on PvP servers is. <br>
<br>
a. Always travel in groups if you can.<br>
b. Keep the MR maxxed.<br>
<br>
Remember on a PvP server its mostly not honorable dueling... it more like ambush/bushwack. A wizzy isn't likely to manaburn someone in a large strong group. Usually they pick off the strays. <br>
<br>
